verbose_text: We also found that anti-DNA Ab (Farr) titers correlated better with IgM-anti-dsDNA Ab titers (r = 0.500 p = 0.0001) than IgG-anti-dsDNA Ab titers (r = 0.246, p = 0.0026), which further supports that the increased levels of serum anti-DNA Ab (Farr) reflected the increase of IgM-anti-dsDNA Ab in our cohort.
